Q.1. Who has written this article “January Night”?
(A) Premchand
(B) Dr. Rana S. P. Singh
(C) Anton Chekov
(D) John Galsworthy
Answer: (A) Premchand
Explanation: “January Night” is written by Premchand, a famous Hindi writer and novelist.

Q.2. Premchand is originally known as?
(A) Dhanpat Pandey
(B) Dhanpat Rai
(C) Dhanpat Mistri
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) Dhanpat Rai
Explanation: Premchand’s original name was Dhanpat Rai.

Q.3. Which of the following work of Premchand was banned by the British Govt.?
(A) Godan
(B) Nirmala
(C) Soz-e-Watan
(D) None of these
Answer: (C) Soz-e-Watan
Explanation: “Soz-e-Watan” (a collection of patriotic stories) was banned by the British government for sedition.

Q.4. Who was Halku?
(A) A Washerman
(B) A tenant farmer
(C) A Goldsmith
(D) None of these
Answer: (B) A tenant farmer
Explanation: Halku was a poor tenant farmer who struggled to pay his debts.

Q.5. What kind of woman was Munni?
(A) She was the wife of Halku
(B) She was a typical housewife
(C) She was very concerned about her income and husband
(D) All of the above
Answer: (D) All of the above
Explanation: Munni was Halku’s wife, a typical housewife, and worried about their income.
+1

Q.6. Halku worked as:
(A) A tenant farmer
(B) An Engineer
(C) A supervisor
(D) A doctor
Answer: (A) A tenant farmer
Explanation: Halku worked as a tenant farmer.

Q.7. Munni advised Halku to hire himself out as a:
(A) Tenant
(B) Labourer
(C) Farmer
(D) Shopkeeper
Answer: (B) Labourer
Explanation: Munni advised him to work as a labourer to earn money rather than farming someone else's land at a loss.

Q.8. Halku heard some munching and crunching sounds coming from the:
(A) House
(B) Fields
(C) Terrace
(D) Groves
Answer: (B) Fields
Explanation: He heard animals eating crops in the field.

Q.9. Munni asked Halku how he could have ________ peacefully when his crops were being destroyed.
(A) Slept
(B) Jumped
(C) Eaten
(D) Travelled
Answer: (A) Slept
Explanation: Munni asked how he could sleep while animals were destroying the crops.

Q.10. At the end of the story, Halku is:
(A) Sad
(B) Confused
(C) Angry
(D) Contented
Answer: (D) Contented
Explanation: Halku felt relieved because now he would not have to guard the field in cold poos (January) nights.

Q.11. Who was ‘Jabra’?
(A) dog
(B) sheep
(C) ox
(D) monkey
Answer: (A) dog
Explanation: Jabra was Halku’s dog.

Q.12. Jabra looked ………….. at the fire.
(A) wagged
(B) fright
(C) fearfully
(D) warm
Answer: (C) fearfully
Explanation: Jabra looked fearfully at the fire.

Q.13. The bitter truth in Halku’s words came charging at her like a wild…………………..
(A) crow
(B) animal
(C) beast
(D) bird
Answer: (C) beast
Explanation: The harsh truth hit Munni like a wild beast.

Q.14. Halku curled up drawing his ………….. close against his chin.
(A) feet
(B) knees
(C) mouth
(D) hands
Answer: (B) knees
Explanation: Halku curled up and pulled his knees close to his chin to keep warm.

Q.15. Munshi Premchand died in………
(A) 1926
(B) 1936
(C) 1896
(D) 1836
Answer: (B) 1936
Explanation: Premchand died in 1936.

